The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem in computational geometry, specifically the two-dimensional strip packing problem. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a likely sub-category. The paper also presents an algorithm with improved approximation ratio, which falls under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of lower bounds and approximation ratios suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper involves optimization and algorithmic game theory, which could make it relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
